        After starting his career at National Instruments supporting, teaching and developing LabVIEW, Robert Mortensen decided he liked using LabVIEW more than making it.  So he left NI and worked for integration companies Moore Good Ideas and VPI Engineering while honing his LabVIEW skills and earning his MBA.  Armed with his CLA (LabVIEW Architect Certification), extensive LabVIEW experience and a desire to use his business training, he founded Endigit in 2011.  The name Endigit is a compilation of the concepts of engineering and the digital world.  It encompasses Robert's vision for a solid company providing quality services and products.
