      %p
        Shawn Walpole started programming with Microsoft Basic on the Apple Macintosh 128k computer in the 1980s and has loved it ever since.  He graduated with a Mechanical Engineering BS degree and a Computer Science minor from the University of Utah in 2000.  He worked on the LabVIEW R&amp;D team at National Instruments for four years developing LabVIEW before moving to Moore Good Ideas.  Shawn was impressed by Endigit's vision and joined the Endigit team in 2014.
      %p
        Shawn gets job satisfaction out of meeting customer needs.  He likes LabVIEW because well-written code is easy to read and because of the power of a development environment that was written for programmers working with real hardware.
      %p
        Shawn has industry experience programming LabVIEW and C/C++.  He has worked with Real Time, FPGA, DAQmx, Motion, TestStand, and Veristand. He has 9 years experience as a LabVIEW consultant with many project successes.
