      %p
        Before discovering LabVIEW, Carl Wecker had a varied background ranging from programming, R&amp;D Engineering and working with artificial hearts to construction, masonry, and real estate. During his 6 years working at Maxtec in Salt Lake City, Carl became immersed in LabVIEW and hasn't looked back. He jumped from developing test systems and calibration routines for medical gas sensors at Maxtec to working for ATK and developing test software for NASA's SLS program, which will hopefully one day take us to Mars.
      %p
        Carl joined Robert and Shawn in 2015 and is excited to be working with people not only so talented but also so visionary and full of integrity. He comes from a family of programmers and loves all things engineering, especially when it involves software. He graduated with a bachelors in Biomedical Engineering from the University of Utah in 2005.
      %p
